    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-03-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-03-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="315"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d315">
                <head>No. 315.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-03-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 26, 1887</date>. (Received April
                        5.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 475.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith two printed
                    copies of a note<note n="*" xml:id="d315fn1">Printed as amended by Mr. White’s,
                        No. 478, <ref target="#pg_469">p. 469</ref>, <hi rend="italic">infra.</hi>
                    </note> which I have received from the Marquis of Salisbury, in reply to the
                    proposals for a <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi>, contained in your
                    instruction numbered 459, of November 12 last, to Mr. Phelps.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry White.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
